name: The Carbon Cycle AI one
description: "The Carbon Cycle" is an acrylic painting I did in 2019, an artist's take on scientific cycle diagrams like The Water Cycle. The arrows in such diagrams in this case are filled with female forms, evoking the angels of classic religious art. The cross-section at the bottom shows geological symbols. I built Mount Rainier over Seattle and the distant Mt. Adams and Mt. St. Helens in 3D using luminance height maps, then painted them."The Carbon Cycle AI one" is Artificial-Intelligence assisted.
